race.comment: Tricky. MASHEAN (10) has a wide gate but rates strongly. Was switched from the Sydney barn and quickly showed form, leading and placing at the Sunshine Coast. She is still well shy of her best and can win with average luck. SPOILT ROTTEN (4) resumed as a $3.0 favourite at Gatton but didn't put in. He's since won a trial here easily and is likely back on track. Draws awkwardly but has good ability and is worth another chance. HEAD OF THE RIVER (8) resumed much improved placing in stronger at the Sunshine Coast. She was cruelled by a wide barrier and the Gold Coast following and forgive that. Draws well today and will sit closer. Carries just 54kg with the claim and gets her chance. OUTATICK (12) resumed at big odds at Eagle Farm but did a good job beaten 3.5L. Jumps from the rail and has the blinkers on for the first time. May improve into the money with Lloyd replacing the 3kg apprentice. THE GRAND DUCHY (5) is a betting watch on debut. Owns an easy trial win on the inner track.
